## Context

- keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas: Implemented Phase 1-3 pipeline
- Phase 1: Classified 65 KEAP1/NRF2-altered lines (35 KEAP1-loss, 31 NFE2L2-GOF, 1 both)
  - 5 qualifying lineages: Lung (18), Esophagus/Stomach (6), Head/Neck (5), Bladder (4), Uterus (3)
  - All NRF2 target genes validate (NQO1, GCLM, TXNRD1, HMOX1, AKR1C1; p < 0.001)
  - Co-mutations: STK11=11, KRAS=12, KL-subtype=10
- Phase 2: Genome-wide screen (18,435 genes, 6 contexts)
  - 5 SL hits (FDR<0.1, |d|>0.5): NFE2L2 (d=-1.78, pathway), SUCO (d=-0.82), EID3 (d=-0.74), SLC33A1 (d=-0.72)
  - 3 high-confidence (FDR<0.05, |d|>0.8)
  - UXS1: d=-0.575 pan-cancer but FDR=0.31 (not significant yet)
  - ATR: d=-0.069 pan-cancer (no CRISPR signal)
- Phase 3: Lineage-specific hits with UXS1/ATR evaluation
  - UXS1 large effect in Lung (d=-0.83), Bladder (d=-1.01) but FDR not significant
  - ATR null in CRISPR; clinical effect may be pharmacological not genetic
- Next: Phase 4 (PRISM drug sensitivity) not yet tasked; analyst to annotate SUCO/EID3/SLC33A1
- Code: src/cancer/keap1_nrf2_pancancer_dependency_atlas/01-03
- Output: output/cancer/keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas/phase1-3
